        "body": "## Pull request overview\n\nFixes two correctness issues in the consensus and workflow runner-selection logic that could otherwise cause false quorum decisions or cross-architecture disagreement on deterministic runner selection.\n\n**Changes:**\n- Update runner selection hash input to encode `step_index` as fixed-width `u64` LE bytes (instead of architecture-dependent `usize` bytes).\n- Fix `has_consensus_with` in Boolean/Ternary threshold consensus to avoid double-counting when the queried attestation is already present.\n- Add regression tests for both behaviors.\n\n### Reviewed changes\n\nCopilot reviewed 4 out of 4 changed files in this pull request and generated 3 comments.\n\n| File | Description |\n| ---- | ----------- |\n| `src/lib/consensus/src/impls/ternary.rs` | Adjusts `has_consensus_with` logic and adds a regression test for duplicate-attestation handling. |\n| `src/lib/consensus/src/impls/boolean.rs` | Adjusts `has_consensus_with` logic and adds a regression test for duplicate-attestation handling. |\n| `src/core/consensus/src/v1/state/state_004_awaiting_step_run_attestations.rs` | Switches step index hashing to `(usize as u64).to_le_bytes()` for deterministic runner selection. |\n| `src/core/consensus/src/v1/state/state_001_awaiting_trigger.rs` | Switches step index hashing to `(usize as u64).to_le_bytes()` and adds a test intended to document the encoding contract. |\n\n\n\n\n\n---\n\n\ud83d\udca1 <a href=\"/acme/protocol/new/master?filename=.github/instructions/*.instructions.md\" class=\"Link--inTextBlock\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Add Copilot custom instructions</a> for smarter, more guided reviews. <a href=\"https://docs.github.com/en/copilot/customizing-copilot/adding-repository-custom-instructions-for-github-copilot\" class=\"Link--inTextBlock\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">Learn how to get started</a>.",
